        <num>CC 2443</num>
        <heading>2443.  Purchase of a thing already owned</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2443.  Purchase of a thing already owned
A person cannot purchase a thing he already owns.  Nevertheless, the owner of a thing may purchase the rights of a person who has, or may have, an adverse claim to the thing.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
